Structuralism from Macmillan Dictionary of Anthropology

linguistics, anthropology, philosophy, literary criticism

the study of language as system of signs relating to structural principles
	surface structures and deep structures

culture is surface phenomenon
	human tendency to organise and categorise perceptions and experience

underlying ordering principles are the same - Binary Oppositions

mental and cultural systems use contrast to differentiate
	nothing is understood in isolation, only as part of a binary/contrasting pair
	left/right - centre/periphery - occident/orient

constitutes a general science of communication and sociocultural behaviour

has a relationship to Marxist BASE/Superstructure analysis of society

Criticisms - it is STATIC and AHISTORICAL
